# Cloudflare Pages reads this file from the publish dir and applies the
# rewrite/redirect rules in order. See:
# https://developers.cloudflare.com/pages/configuration/redirects/
#
# .well-known files (security.txt, etc.) must bypass the SPA fallback so they
# return the actual file with text/plain rather than the Angular HTML shell.
# CF Pages serves real files in publish dir before evaluating redirects, so
# this rule is defence-in-depth in case a future build ever omits the file
# (a 404 beats a 200 HTML payload masquerading as security.txt).
/.well-known/*  /.well-known/:splat  200

# SPA fallback — any unknown path serves the Angular shell so client-side
# routing takes over.
/*  /index.html  200
